Package edu.biu.scapi.interactiveMidProtocols.coinTossing

Interface Summary
CTOutput Each coin tossing protocol outputs different "coin".
CTPartyOne Coin tossing is the practice of throwing a coin in the air to choose between two alternatives, sometimes to resolve a dispute between two parties.
CTPartyTwo Coin tossing is the practice of throwing a coin in the air to choose between two alternatives, sometimes to resolve a dispute between two parties.
 

Class Summary
CTBitOutput Concrete output class that outputs a single bit.
CTBlumPartyOne This class plays as party one of coin tossing Blum protocol, which tosses a single bit.
CTBlumPartyTwo This class plays as party two of coin tossing Blum protocol, which tosses a single bit.
CTSemiSimulatablePartyOne This class plays as party one of coin tossing protocol which tosses a string.
CTSemiSimulatablePartyTwo This class plays as party two of coin tossing protocol which tosses a string.
CTStringOutput Concrete output class that outputs a String.
CTStringPartyOne Concrete implementation of a protocol for tossing a string from party one's point of view.
CTStringPartyTwo Concrete implementation of a protocol for tossing a string from party two's point of view.
